From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 18:18:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 23/23] Perf: run KVSync boundary push detached (stop blocking
 session close)

Upstream issue: (pai-nix — performance; no upstream issue.)

KVSync runs at SessionStart and SessionEnd. It awaits a network push
(pushStateToTargets + pushEventsToTargets, each with 5-8s timeouts in
observability-transport) before the hook process exits. Because the
session waits for its boundary hooks, that round-trip is added
directly to session start and, more noticeably, session CLOSE latency
— on a slow or unreachable target the user waits multiple seconds for
the session to close while the dashboard sync drains its timeout.

This decouples the push from the session lifecycle by performing it in
a DETACHED child process:

  - Parent mode (the hook invocation): reads stdin (hook protocol),
    spawns a detached child re-running this same file with
    KVSYNC_DETACHED=1, calls child.unref(), prints { continue: true },
    and exits immediately. The session no longer waits on the network.
  - Child mode (KVSYNC_DETACHED=1): imports observability-transport and
    performs the actual push, outliving the parent (detached + setsid,
    stdio ignored) so the work completes in the background.

NOT a functional removal. The push still happens on every boundary;
local-target sync (the Pulse dashboard on localhost:31337) is fully
preserved — only the blocking wait is removed. This is deliberately
scoped to KVSync alone; UpdateCounts.hook.ts has the same
block-on-network-at-SessionEnd shape (Anthropic usage/cost API,
3-5s timeouts) and is a candidate for an equivalent follow-up patch,
kept separate for clean blame/rollback.

Doc comment updated to drop the stale "Cloudflare KV"-specific wording
(post-0023 the hook is generic over observability targets, and after
patch 0022 the shipped default has no cloudflare-kv target at all).

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts   :1-23 (whole body)

Total: 1 file, 1 hunk.

Verification: `bun build --no-bundle` parses the rewritten file;
invoking the hook with a SessionEnd payload returns in ~60ms (bun
startup only, no network wait) versus the prior await-bound time; a
detached child process is spawned and performs the push independently.
Hunk generated via `diff -u` against the upstream v5.0.0 source tree.
---
 Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts | 42 ++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 30 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts
--- a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/KVSync.hook.ts
@@ -1,23 +1,41 @@
 #!/usr/bin/env bun
 /**
- * KVSync.hook.ts — Push work.json to Cloudflare KV at session boundaries
+ * KVSync.hook.ts — Push work.json to observability targets at session boundaries
  *
  * TRIGGER: SessionStart, SessionEnd
  *
- * Ensures KV always has fresh work.json data regardless of whether ISASync
- * fires during the session. Prevents the recurring "activity page empty"
- * issue caused by KV going stale between sessions.
+ * Ensures targets always have fresh work.json data regardless of whether
+ * ISASync fires during the session. Prevents the recurring "activity page
+ * empty" issue caused by state going stale between sessions.
+ *
+ * The push runs in a DETACHED child process so the network round-trip
+ * (5-8s timeouts in observability-transport) never blocks session start or
+ * close. The parent returns immediately; the detached child outlives it and
+ * completes the push in the background. Local-target sync (e.g. the Pulse
+ * dashboard on localhost) is fully preserved — only the blocking wait is gone.
  */
 
 import { readFileSync } from 'fs';
-import { pushStateToTargets, pushEventsToTargets } from './lib/observability-transport';
+import { spawn } from 'child_process';
+
+// Child mode: perform the actual push, decoupled from the session lifecycle.
+if (process.env.KVSYNC_DETACHED === '1') {
+  const { pushStateToTargets, pushEventsToTargets } = await import('./lib/observability-transport');
+  await Promise.all([pushStateToTargets(), pushEventsToTargets()])
+    .catch((err) => console.error(`[KVSync] Fatal: ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`));
+  process.exit(0);
+}
 
-// Read stdin (required by hook protocol) but we don't need the input
+// Parent mode: read stdin (hook protocol), spawn the detached pusher, return
+// immediately so the session never waits on the network round-trip.
 try { readFileSync(0, 'utf-8'); } catch {}
 
-Promise.all([pushStateToTargets(), pushEventsToTargets()])
-  .catch((err) => console.error(`[KVSync] Fatal: ${err.message}`))
-  .finally(() => {
-    console.log(JSON.stringify({ continue: true }));
-    process.exit(0);
-  });
+const child = spawn(process.execPath, [import.meta.path], {
+  detached: true,
+  stdio: 'ignore',
+  env: { ...process.env, KVSYNC_DETACHED: '1' },
+});
+child.unref();
+
+console.log(JSON.stringify({ continue: true }));
+process.exit(0);
